# Requirements Baseline

## Product
- Name: Pet Vet Coding Puzzles.
- Platform: modern desktop browser.
- Audience: beginner learners who can read simple instructions.

## Learning And Gameplay Requirements
- The game must teach sequencing, loops, and conditionals through puzzle progression.
- Exactly 17 playable puzzles are required.
- Core loop must be implemented as: open puzzle, read story and goal, drag blocks into connected sequence under On Start, press Play, observe animation, receive Oops plus hint on failure, unlock next puzzle on success.
- Puzzle progression must enforce lock/unlock state.
- Hint messages must map to deterministic failure reasons and must not immediately reveal full solutions.

## Frontend Requirements
- Provide a visual block workspace with command library and active code area.
- Render the veterinary clinic themed scene and goal context.
- Execute only connected blocks under On Start.
- Disconnected blocks must trigger a warning and must not execute.
- Implement deterministic runtime behavior with loop safety cap and collision failure reason handling.
- Support keyboard navigation for major controls.
- Use large controls, clear labels, readable contrast, and avoid conveying critical information by color alone.

## Backend Requirements
- Provide HTTP service with SQLite persistence.
- Required endpoints:
  - "'`GET /health`
  - `GET /api/levels`
  - `GET /api/levels/:id`
  - `POST /api/session/start`
  - `POST /api/session/end`
  - `POST /api/events/batch`
  - `GET /api/analytics/dashboard`
  - `GET /api/analytics/puzzle/:id`
  - `GET /api/analytics/events`
- Frontend runtime flow must retrieve levels and submit telemetry through backend endpoints.

## Data And Persistence Requirements
- Puzzle records must be data-driven with fields: `id`, `title`, `storyText`, `goalText`, `scene`, `grid`, `entities`, `availableBlocks`, `constraints`, `successCriteria`, `hintRules`.
- SQLite must auto-initialize on first backend start.
- Required tables: `users`, `sessions`, `puzzles`, `attempts`, `events`, `movements`, `puzzle_progress`.
- Telemetry must persist movement and execution events without dropping movement or execution steps.
- Analytics must support local replay from persisted movement data.

## Safety And Privacy Requirements
- No personal data collection is required for core gameplay.
- No third-party authentication is required for core gameplay.
- Analytics remain local to the application environment.

## Acceptance Requirements
- All 17 puzzles are playable.
- Failure runs show Oops plus at least one helpful hint.
- Success runs complete goals and unlock progression.
- Telemetry and movement persistence are verifiable in SQLite.
- Analytics replay from persisted movement records is verifiable.
- Deterministic local test suite must pass before acceptance.
