===== REQUIREMENTS.md =====
# Requirements Baseline

## Product
- Name: Pet Vet Coding Puzzles.
- Platform: modern desktop browser.
- Audience: beginner learners who can read simple instructions.

## Learning And Gameplay Requirements
- The game must teach sequencing, loops, and conditionals through puzzle progression.
- Exactly 17 playable puzzles are required.
- Core loop must be implemented as: open puzzle, read story and goal, drag blocks into connected sequence under On Start, press Play, observe animation, receive Oops plus hint on failure, unlock next puzzle on success.
- Puzzle progression must enforce lock/unlock state.
- Hint messages must map to deterministic failure reasons and must not immediately reveal full solutions.

## Frontend Requirements
- Provide a visual block workspace with command library and active code area.
- Render the veterinary clinic themed scene and goal context.
- Execute only connected blocks under On Start.
- Disconnected blocks must trigger a warning and must not execute.
